Reds 6, Mets 2
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   CINCINNATI (AP) -- Ken Griffey Jr. returned to the lineup and hit his 37th
homer Sunday -- a rare left-handed shot off Al Leiter -- as the Cincinnati Reds
beat New York 6-2, the Mets' fourth consecutive loss. Since catching Atlanta
atop the NL East, the Mets have dropped five of six, costing them a chance to
open a lead while the Braves struggled.
</P>
