<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Girl Accused of Murdering Her Mom  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SCHAUMBURG, Ill. (AP) -- A 13-year-old girl was charged with
first-degree murder Monday in the death of her mother, who had been
stabbed repeatedly as she sat in her car.
</P>
<P>
   Je Taun Walters, 34, died after she was stabbed with a kitchen
knife Saturday outside her apartment in this northwestern Chicago
suburb.
</P>
<P>
   Police filed a juvenile petition seeking murder charges against
the daughter after she ''made statements implicating herself,''
Sgt. Paul Rizzo said. He declined to say whether she had confessed
or if police knew of a motive.
</P>
<P>
   The teen-ager initially told officers she and her mother had
left their apartment to run an errand, according to police. She
said that her mother had forgotten something and told her to go
back for it, and that when she returned 10 minutes later, her
mother was slumped over on the blood-stained passenger seat, police
said.
</P>
<P>
   The youth was treated at a hospital for minor injuries, which
she said she suffered while trying to pull her mother from the car.
</P>
<P>
   Rizzo said Monday that ''certain things just didn't make sense''
about the girl's account of events, and she had the types of
injuries that ''might lend themselves more to an offender than a
victim.''
</P>
<P>
   He wouldn't rule out that possibility that another person could
be charged.
</P>
<P>
   Police were alerted to the stabbing by tracing two 911 hangups
to the slain woman's apartment -- apparently placed by young
cousins.
</P>
</TEXT>
