<HEADLINE> Moderate Quake Jolts Western India  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW DELHI, India (AP) -- An earthquake of moderate intensity
shook the western Indian state of Maharashtra early Tuesday, the
Press Trust of India reported. There were no immediate reports of
damage or injuries.
</P>
<P>
   The magnitude-5.0 quake had its epicenter in Warna, 705 miles
south of India's capital of New Delhi, weather department officials
told PTI.
</P>
<P>
   Tremors were felt in Bombay, India's financial hub and the state
capital, PTI said.
</P>
<P>
   Government workers had left for remote villages to assess the
damage, PTI said.
</P>
