<HEADLINE> Boyfriend charged with killing woman, 2 children in apartment  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   YONKERS, N.Y. (AP) - A 23-year-old Yonkers man was charged
Monday with stabbing to death his live-in girlfriend and two of her
young children.
</P>
<P>
   Dennis Salvador Alvarez was charged with three counts of
second-degree murder in the killings of Patricia Torres, 28, Ashley
Dominguez, 4, and William Santiago, 7, who were found dead in their
apartment Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
   After stabbing his girlfriend and her children several times
each with a penknife, Alvarez stabbed himself in the neck and chest
but survived, police said. He was arraigned while in stable
condition in a St. Joseph's Medical Center bed and was being held
without bail.
</P>
<P>
   Another of the woman's children, Vincent Torres, 9, also was
stabbed in the neck and chest but managed to climb out a window of
the first-floor apartment and scamper to his grandparents'
apartment next door, family members said. The boy was hospitalized
in critical condition.
</P>
<P>
   Alvarez and the girlfriend he allegedly stabbed to death had a
history of violent domestic disputes, Westchester County District
Attorney Jeanine Pirro said.
</P>
<P>
   Alvarez began dating Torres last year and soon moved into the
apartment she shared with her children, all from previous
boyfriends. Another of Torres' children, Rodolfo Torres, 10, lives
with his grandparents.
</P>
</TEXT>
