<HEADLINE> Swiss Fireman Admits Setting Fires  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PRATTELN, Switzerland (AP) -- A Swiss fireman has been arrested
for starting 21 fires over the past two years, Basel state police
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The 39-year-old, who was not identified, admitted setting the
fires, mostly in wooden sheds and in the basements of apartment
buildings, beginning in September 1998. He was caught at the end of
last month after setting a shack ablaze in this northwestern town.
</P>
<P>
   The fires caused more than $290,000 worth of damage but no
injuries, police said.
</P>
