<HEADLINE> Cops Find Ton of Hashish on Beach  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALGECIRAS, Spain (AP) -- Police dug up 2,530 pounds of hashish
buried in the sand of a beach at Spain's southern tip, authorities
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Spain's Civil Guard -- which controls the borders and seacoast --
said environmental protection agents found the 46 packages of
hashish Monday at Linea de la Concepcion at Spain's southern tip
right next to Gibraltar. Each package contained about 55 pounds of
hashish.
</P>
<P>
   The Civil Guard said police had made no arrests. Authorities did
not say how agents found the hashish.
</P>
<P>
   Much of the hashish that enters Spain comes on boats from
northern Africa, particularly Morocco.
