<HEADLINE> Dow Adds 48; Nasdaq Drops 51  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were mixed Tuesday, as investors returned
from a holiday weekend to a market with little news to influence
trading.
</P>
<P>
   In midafternoon trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial
average was up 48.09 at 11,286.87.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq composite index fell 51.38 to 4,182.95. The Standard
&AMP; Poor's 500 index dropped 9.60 to 1511.17.
</P>
<P>
   With no big news to provide a clear direction for trading, the
market drifted, with indexes alternating between positive and
negative territory.
</P>
<P>
   ''September has typically been a very unclear month for the
market and after the very nice run we had in August, we've got some
profit-taking and maybe some developing concerns about reports for
third-quarter earnings,'' said Bill Barker, an investment strategy
consultant with Dain Rauscher Inc. in Dallas.
</P>
<P>
   Eugene Mintz, a financial markets analyst at Brown Brothers
Harriman &AMP; Co, said the economy appears to be slowing, and many
investors aren't sure what that means for their portfolios. Barring
any major corporate announcement or other financial news, Mintz
said it might take time for the market to find direction.
</P>
<P>
   ''It looks pretty much like people are just sitting back and
saying, 'We'll wait and see for a while before doing anything,'''
he said.
</P>
<P>
   Shares of Niagara Mohawk Holdings rose $1.75 to $15.63 after
British-based National Grid Group PLC announced it was buying the
utility for $3 billion in cash and stock. Niagara Mohawk is the
second-largest electric and gas provider in New York state.
</P>
<P>
   Fisher Scientific International's shares jumped $10.81 to
$32.75. The company announced late Friday its $800 million plan to
buy PSS World Medical Inc., another medical products distributor,
had fallen apart. The plan was not popular with investors.
</P>
<P>
   Intel fell $4.88 to $69.06 in early trading after a U.S. Bancorp
Piper Jaffray analyst downgraded the computer chip maker's stock to
''buy'' from ''strong buy.''
</P>
<P>
   Advancing issues trailed decliners by a narrow margin on the New
York Stock Exchanges, where volume came to 559.60 million shares.
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index was down 0.11 to 541.80.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
