<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 7; Nasdaq Falls 73  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Tech and pharmaceutical stocks fell amid
earnings warnings from analysts Tuesday, while the broader market
drifted in lackluster trading.
</P>
<P>
   In late afternoon on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial
average was up 7.40 at 11,246.18.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq composite index fell 73.01 to 4,161.32. The Standard
&AMP; Poor's 500 index slipped 14.45 to 1,506.32.
</P>
<P>
   With no big news to provide a clear direction for trading, the
market meandered, with indexes alternating between positive and
negative territory.
</P>
<P>
   ''September has typically been a very unclear month for the
market and after the very nice run we had in August, we've got some
profit-taking and maybe some developing concerns about reports for
third-quarter earnings,'' said Bill Barker, an investment strategy
consultant with Dain Rauscher Inc. in Dallas.
</P>
<P>
   The exceptions were the pharamceutical and tech sectors, which
fell overall.
</P>
<P>
   Intel fell $4.88 to $69.06 in early trading after a U.S. Bancorp
Piper Jaffray analyst downgraded the computer chip maker's stock to
''buy'' from ''strong buy. Ashok Kumar said he was concerned that
continued weakness in demand could result in unit growth ''well
below consensus expectations.''
</P>
<P>
   Computer maker stocks also fell, with Gateway dropping $4.59 to
$64.09 and Dell off $2.66 at $40.41.
</P>
<P>
   Pharmaceutical stocks fell slightly after Banc of America
Securities downgraded Merck to ''market perform'' from ''strong
buy'' and, at the same time, reduced estimates for the overall
pharmaceutical sector.
</P>
<P>
   Merck traded at $67.75, down $1.44. Pfizer was down $2.34 at
$40.81.
</P>
<P>
   Advancing issues trailed decliners by a narrow margin on the New
York Stock Exchanges, where volume came to 559.60 million shares.
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index was down 1.10 at 540.81.
</P>
<P>
   ------
