<HEADLINE> Tigers Activate Mlicki, Morris  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DETROIT (AP) -- The Detroit Tigers on Tuesday activated
right-hander pitcher Dave Mlicki and first baseman Hal Morris, who
had been on the 15-day disabled list.
</P>
<P>
   The Tigers also recalled first baseman/outfielder Dusty Allen
from Triple-A Toledo and purchased left-hander Kevin Tolar's
contract from Toledo.
</P>
<P>
   Mlicki was placed on the disabled list July 23 due to a chronic
sinus infection. He was 4-10, with a 5.61 ERA for the Tigers.
</P>
<P>
   Morris went on the disabled list Aug. 9 with a fractured left
index finger. He was batting .296 for the Tigers since being
acquired from the Cincinnati Reds on July 18.
</P>
<P>
   Allen was optioned Friday and was first recalled by the Tigers
on Aug. 9 when Morris was injured. He is batting .400 for the
Tigers.
</P>
<P>
   Tolar was 4-2 with a 3.30 ERA in 33 games for Toledo. He will
make his major league debut with the Tigers.
</P>
<P>
   To make room on the 40-man roster for Tolar, pitcher Brandon
Villafuerte was designated for assignment.
</P>
