<HEADLINE> N.C. Cops Look for Gunman in Clinic  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ASHEVILLE, N.C. (AP) -- Police searched Tuesday for a man who
brandished a gun at a health clinic and demanded to see his
children.
</P>
<P>
   The unidentified man vanished from the Buncombe County Health
Center after pulling out a weapon in front of a receptionist
Tuesday morning. Some 200 employees and patients were evacuated
from the center, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   ''.. (He) pulled a pistol, then he told the receptionist he
wanted his kids,'' said assistant health director Nancy Thompson.
</P>
<P>
   There was no indication his children were actually at the
center. City spokeswoman Robin Nix said there had been no reports
of gunshots.
</P>
<P>
   Nearly two dozen officers with dogs searched in vain for the
man, who was described as dark-haired, about 5 feet 9 inches tall,
weighing 165 pounds and wearing a blue checked shirt and a baseball
cap.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
