<HEADLINE> Sosa Receiving Hispanic Award  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER (AP) -- Five days before its actual presentation, Sammy
Sosa shot a television spot highlighting his acceptance and
acknowledgment of a 2000 Hispanic Heritage Award.
</P>
<P>
   ''This is impressive, especially considering where I came
from,'' Sosa said. ''To receive the award is big for me. It is big
and makes me proud to be a member of the Hispanic community and not
just its athletes.''
</P>
<P>
   The spot was taped prior to the Chicago Cubs-Colorado Rockies
game Tuesday at Coors Field.
</P>
<P>
   The Cubs outfielder is one of five recipients honored by the
Hispanic Heritage Awards Foundation.
</P>
<P>
   Widely recognized as the most prestigious honor in the Hispanic
community, Hispanic Heritage Awards honors individuals in the
categories of the arts, literature, leadership, education and
sports.
</P>
<P>
   Actor Anthony Quinn, Pulitzer Prize novelist Oscar Hijuelos,
UCLA law professor Cruz Reynoso and labor organizer Delores Huerta
join Sosa as their year's recipients.
</P>
<P>
   Hall of Fame offensive guard Anthony Munoz and Olympian Rebecca
Lobo made the presentation.
</P>
<P>
   ''I think I am a better person because of what I do off the
field,'' Sosa said. ''The team gives me those opportunities.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
