<HEADLINE> BoSox Pichardo Leaves Game  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON (AP) -- Boston Red Sox reliever Hipolito Pichardo left
Tuesday night's game against the Oakland Athletics with an apparent
elbow problem.
</P>
<P>
   Pichardo relieved Pete Schourek with one out in the seventh
inning with runners on first and third and Boston leading 8-1. He
allowed a double to Mike Stanley, then Adam Piatt grounded into a
fielder's choice.
</P>
<P>
   Pichardo then walked Ben Grieve and Miguel Tejada before Red Sox
first baseman Jose Offerman came to the mound and pointed to the
right-hander's elbow and home plate umpire Randy Marsh. Red Sox
manager Jimy Williams came to the mound with trainer Jim Rowe, and
then Rich Garces came in to relieve Pichardo.
</P>
<P>
   Pichardo, who threw only three strikes in 12 pitches, has been
one of Boston's most reliable middle relievers this season. He was
5-3 with one save and a 3.15 ERA in 33 appearances coming into the
game.
</P>
