<HEADLINE> California Senator Breaks Leg  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Sen. Dianne Feinstein of California broke her
leg in a fall at her family vacation home in Colorado, her office
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The 67-year-old Democrat slipped on stairs at her Aspen home and
suffered a compound fracture of her left tibia, the larger of the
two bones between the knee and the ankle, said spokesman Howard
Gantman.
</P>
<P>
   She was back in Washington on Tuesday with a cast, but will need
surgery in the next few days, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Feinstein is seeking re-election in November.
</P>
