<HEADLINE> Husband charged with attempted murder of wife  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   STONY POINT, N.Y. (AP) - Police have charged a Queens man with
trying to kill his wife by steering the jeep she was in off the
edge of a 65-foot cliff in Harriman State Park last week.
</P>
<P>
   According to investigators, 47-year-old Cavim Suljovic of Fresh
Meadows was driving along Seven Lakes Drive North with his
39-year-old wife Aferdita and their two sons Thursday when he
stopped and ordered his children out of the car. He then drove his
1990 Jeep Cherokee to the edge of a steep embankment, positioning
the vehicle so his wife could not escape before directing it toward
the ledge and jumping out himself.
</P>
<P>
   Aferdita Suljovic suffered numerous cuts and bruises as well as
first-, second- and third-degree burns when the vehicle flipped
over the ledge and caught on fire. It was unknown whether she was
wearing a seat belt.
</P>
<P>
   She was airlifted to Westchester Medical Center, where she was
listed in critical but stable condition. A hospital spokesman
Tuesday night withheld further information at the patient's
request.
</P>
<P>
   Cavim Suljovic was arrested when he came to the hospital Sunday.
He is being held at Rockland County Jail on $500,000 bail. He is
due to answer an attempted murder charge in Orangetown Court
Wednesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
