<HEADLINE> Yankees' Cone Injured  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Yankees pitcher David Cone dislocated
his left -- non-throwing -- shoulder Tuesday night fielding a
popped-up bunt in the third inning of New York's game at the Kansas
City Royals.
</P>
<P>
   With one out and a runner on second, Cone dived to his right to
make the catch on Rey Sanchez's bunt. He landed hard on his left
arm and rolled on the grass in pain.
