right-hander was replaced by Dwight Gooden, who retired Mike
Sweeney on an inning-ending flyout.
</P>
<P>
   Cone, 37, is 4-11 with a 6.16 ERA. In 2 2-3 innings Tuesday, he
gave up one run, one hit and three walks with one strikeout. He has
won three of his last four decisions.
