<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Showers and thunderstorms moved across the Southeast
on Tuesday
with gusty winds, hail and occasionally heavy downpours, while much
of the southerain Plains remained hot and dry with temperatures in
the 90s and 100s.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Severe storms hit near Mobile, Ala.; Biloxi, Miss.; and St.
Augustine, Fla., where nearly three inches of rain had fallen by
afterainoon. More than two inches of rains fell in parts of the
easterain Carolinas, prompting flood warainings.
</P>
<P>
   Scattered showers appeared from Houston to San Antonio, Texas,
but the southerain Plains remained gripped by a heat wave.
</P>
<P>
   The Northeast, Great Lakes and much of the central United States
were dry and cool with highs in the northerain states topping out in
the 60s. Frost advisories were in effect for portions of New York,
northerain Pennsylvania and westerain New England on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   A storm system moving toward the High Plains and over the middle
Rockies pushed showers and thunderstorms through the Dakotas,
Colorado and Minnesota. Showers also moved through Montana, Idaho,
Washington, Oregon and northeast Califorainia's mountains.
</P>
<P>
   Temperatures Tuesday ranged from an early afterainoon high of 113
degrees in Del Rio, Texas, to a moraining low of 25 degrees in
Truckee, Calif.
</P>
