<HEADLINE> MetroStars 2, Fusion 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Adolfo Valencia made a penalty kick
with eight minutes left as the New York-New Jersey MetroStars beat
the Miami Fusion 2-1 Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   The victory boosted the MetroStars' record to 17-11-3, for an
MLS-high 54 points.
</P>
<P>
   The Fusion (11-15-5) moved closer to missing the playoffs.
Miami, with one game left, is tied for ninth place, two points out
of the eighth and final postseason spot.
</P>
<P>
   Valencia scored his 16th goal of the season, after Tab Ramos was
fouled by Miami defender Jay Hoops, made the score 2-0.
</P>
<P>
   Miami scored a minute later. Diego Serna took Martin Machon's
pass and chipped the ball over MetroStars goalkeeper Paul Grafer.
</P>
<P>
   The game's first goal came 10 minutes in, when the MetroStars'
Mike Petke scored off a rebound from 6 yards out.
</P>
<P>
   Grafer made six saves. He was called up from the A League's Long
Island Rough Riders to replace Tim Howard, the backup goalkeeper on
the U.S. Olympic team.
</P>
<P>
   Mike Ammann, the MetroStars' top goalkeeper, is out for the
season after breaking three ribs in a game last month.
</P>
