<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sierra club endorses Clinton over Lazio  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. (AP) - The Sierra Club endorsed Hillary
Rodham Clinton for Senate on Tuesday, saying her Republican
opponent, Rep. Rick Lazio, has ''dropped the ball'' on several
important environmental issues.
</P>
<P>
   Lazio has been viewed as an ally in the past by other
environmental groups for his efforts to clean up Long Island Sound
and to fight strip-mining. But the Sierra Club touted Clinton's
commitment to environmental issues while saying Lazio hasn't done
enough to protect the state from pollution.
</P>
<P>
   Lazio defended his environmental record and said he ''can't
think of a single time when Mrs. Clinton has ever forcefully spoke
out on any environmental issue.''
</P>
<P>
   The Sierra Club's New York leaders conducted lengthy interviews
with each candidate before making the decision.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-09-05-00 2343 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
